      h1.main FreeCodeCamp API Basejump: Timestamp microservice
      
      
      h3 Use cases:
      div.stories 
        p 1) You can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
        p 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
        p 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
      
      div.examples 
        h3 Example usage:
        p https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/microstamp/December%2015,%202015
        p https://timestamp-ms.herokuapp.com/microstamp/1450137600
      
      div.output
        h3 Example output:
        p { "unix": 1450137600, "natural": "December 15, 2015" }